CHANGELOG
Project: alterEXIFpy3
Format: Semantic Versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)

Version 2.0.0 - 2026-06-26
Modernized Python 3 Release

Added:

Complete Python 3 rewrite of the original alterEXIF script

New command line interface using argparse

Batch processing mode for folders

EXIF backup system (JSON format)

City based GPS spoofing

Random radius GPS spoofing

Altitude spoofing

Logging system with verbose mode

Overwrite protection for destination files

Centralized GPS EXIF builder

Single pass EXIF load and write for improved performance

AI assistance disclosure and documentation updates

Improved:

Code structure and readability

Error handling and input validation

Memory efficiency by closing images immediately

DMS conversion logic (consolidated and standardized)

Folder creation and file handling logic

Fixed:

Crashes when GPS tags were missing

Inconsistent EXIF writes on some JPEGs

Redundant code paths from the legacy version

Removed:

Python 2 specific code

Legacy interactive input prompts

Duplicate EXIF handling logic

Version 1.0.0 - Legacy Release
Original alterEXIF Script (Python 2)

Notes:

Basic GPS EXIF modification

Limited error handling

No batch mode

No EXIF backup

No CLI

No spoofing radius or city presets

Deprecated due to Python 2 end of life
